Thanks for the feedback! I have address all comments so far.

@j-loreaux Thanks for the comments. I have split the untroversial parts of this PR (just adding new lemmas, without changing existing statements) into #22175. Once that has landed, I will see if or how the rest of this PR should get merged, including starting a discussion on zulip as needed.

I have some concerns here. I think sometimes it really is preferably to talk about `nnnorm`. There are some places where the diff seems to increase unnecessarily just because we changed the statements of some lemmas. I think it's possible we should have lemmas about both `enorm` and `nnnorm` (although I don't love the duplication).

I think it's possible we should have lemmas about both `enorm` and `nnnorm` (although I don't love the duplication).

```suggestion
theorem rpow_ofNNReal {M : ‚Ñù‚â•0} {P : ‚Ñù} (hP : 0 ‚â§ P) :
That's not a great name
The name looks fine to me, but the lemma should not be in that file.
Why is there a `deprecated` attribute in a comment here?
Do you want to add that lemma in this PR?
Can you please use the coercion here (via type ascription) to make this easier to read?
This doesn't seem like the statement you want (i.e., it's specialized to `2`). Probably you meant something else?

These aren't strictly aliases though, right? Because one takes place in `‚Ñù‚â•0‚àû` and the other in `‚Ñù‚â•0`. Is there a discussion about this that I missed somewhere? This question applies to many of the changes made in this file.
I'm not sure where this lemma appears, but shouldn't it be called just `enorm_ae...` instead of `coe_enorm_ae...`?
This kind of stuff in the diff makes me skeptical that we really want to be deleting all these results about `nnnorm`.
